nelson peltz  wikipedia nelson peltz from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search nelson peltz born  june   age  brooklyn new york us residence bedford new york palm beach florida alma mater university of pennsylvania occupation investor and fund manager known for founding and leading trian fund management net worth us billion february  board member of wendys company chairman mondelēz international inc ingersoll rand plc legg mason inc spouses wife  divorced wife  divorced claudia heffner children   with heffner nelson peltz born june   is an american investor and fund manager he is a founding partner together with peter w may and edward p garden of trian fund management lp an alternative investment management fund based in new york he is nonexecutive chairman of the board of the wendys company and a director of legg mason mondelēz international and ingersoll rand he was formerly a director of hj heinz company he was also formerly the chief executive officer ceo of triangle industries contents  early life and education  investment career  personal life  wealth and philanthropy  awards and recognition  references  external links early life and educationedit peltz was born to a jewish family in  in brooklyn new york the son of claire née wechsler and maurice herbert peltz peltz was enrolled at the undergraduate program at the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania where he joined the fraternity of phi gamma delta but never completed his degree in  he dropped out of the university of pennsylvania’s wharton school with the intention of becoming a ski instructor in oregon however he ended up driving a delivery truck for a peltz  sons a wholesale food distribution business founded by his grandfather adolph in  which delivered fresh produce and frozen food snow top to restaurants in new york his father gave him free rein with the company and over the next  years he and his older brother robert b peltz grew the business gradually shifting the product line from produce to institutional frozen foods over the next  years peltz bought up several food companies and in  he and his brother took their company then called flagstaff corp with  million in sales public in  his brother robert bought back the assets of peltz food from flagstaff after it went bankrupt investment careeredit in the s peltz and his business partner peter may who had joined flagstaff as chief financial officer after having been its accountant went looking for new acquisitions in april  the two bought a stake in vendingmachine and wire company triangle industries inc with the idea of using it to make acquisitions building it into a fortune  industrial company triangle was sold to pechiney in  in  through an investment vehicle they controlled triarc cos peltz and may acquired snapple from quaker oats snapple together with other beverage brands was sold to cadbury schweppes in  the snapple turnaround was featured as a harvard business school case study in  peltz may and ed garden founded trian fund management lp as an activist investing firm trian has invested in such companies as heinz cadbury kraft foods ingersoll rand wendy’s dupont mondelēz pepsico state street corporation  and family dollar in  trian was involved in a proxy contest with heinz to get five independent directors on the board of heinz trian succeeded in getting two members on the board including peltz in  trian bought a  share of cadburyschweppes cadbury schweppes americas beverages was later spun off from the cadbury schweppes confectionery group in  trian also bought  billion in shares of kraft foods roughly a  of the total equity of the food maker in april  it was announced that triarc cos would merge with burger chain wendys the merger was completed on september   the new company was named wendys arbys group and traded on the new york stock exchange under the symbol wen on july   wendys arbys sold arbys to roark capital group and changed its name to the wendys company according to cnbc on february   trian offered to buy family dollar for – per share in february  trian announced it had accumulated an  stake in the family dollar company and indicated a willingness to participate in a take private lbo for the company with a total value of about  to  billion this overture was rejected by the company management and board of directors in september  ed garden trian’s chief investment officer joined the family dollar board peltz was appointed to the ingersollrand board of directors in  in august  it was reported that trian held an approximate  billion stake in dupont in january  as one of the company’s largest shareholders with a current beneficial ownership of more than  million shares peltz was appointed to the board of directors of global snacking company mondelēz international nasdaq mdlz in february  as a beneficial owner of approximately  billion of pepsico inc nyse pep common shares trian publicly released a letter to pepsico’s board of directors and a white paper detailing why separating global snacks and beverages into two independent public companies would be the right longterm decision for the business and would create substantial value for shareholders trian said it would immediately begin to engage fellow shareholders in a public dialogue with the goal of creating a groundswell of support for a separation of snacks and beverages in february  forbes listed peltz as one of the  highestearning hedge fund managers in  with total earnings of  million ranked th in may  trian was unsuccessful in a bitter proxy contest to appoint four of its nominees to the board of dupont five months later the ceo of dupont ellen kullman resigned at the time dupont acknowledged lower than expected earnings and the need to accelerate a costcutting plan in october  trian bought a  billion stake in general electric personal lifeedit peltzs children will and nicola at the  toronto international film festival peltz has been married three times his third wife is claudia heffner a former fashion model with whom he has eight children he has two children from his prior marriages among peltzs children are actors nicola peltz and will peltz his son brad peltz was a professional ice hockey player who played in the echl during the – echl season peltz resides in bedford new york he also owns montsorrel which is his house in palm beach florida previously owned by anita young the sister of georgia okeeffe he has recently begun a refurbishment and expansion project for the property wealth and philanthropyedit according to forbes magazine he has a net worth of  billion as of february  this makes him the nd richest person in the us in  peltz was among  entities that contributed the maximum of  to the second inauguration of president george w bush he is also a heavy contributor to jewish causes awards and recognitionedit he was recognized by the national association of corporate directors nacd in   and  as among the most influential people in global corporate governance referencesedit  a b nelson peltzs house virtualglobetrottingcom retrieved february     a b forbes the worlds billionaires nelson peltz february   a b c duane d stanford january   mondelez names peltz director as investor seen pushing cuts bloomberg   a b anupreeta das and sharon terlep august   activist peltz wins board seat at ingersoll the wall street journal   a b biography nelson peltz wendys retrieved april     a b shawn tully march   the reinvention of nelson peltz cnnmoneycom   company overview of trian fund management lp bloomberg businessweek retrieved april     fortune  fortune magazine retrieved april     a b c d jewish virtual library nelson peltz by nancy a ruhling retrieved january    maurice peltz  built family food business into a major marketer the new york times    paid notice deaths peltz claire the new york times    wall street frats business insider retrieved  february    a b katherine burton and sree vidya bhaktavatsalam september   peltz gets  b