mbines concentrated public equity ownership with operational expertise leveraging the  years’ operating experience of our principals nelson peltz ed garden and peter may trian seeks to invest in high quality but undervalued and underperforming public companies and to work collaboratively with management teams and boards of those companies to execute operational and strategic initiatives designed to drive longterm sustainable earnings growth for the benefit of all shareholders feedback from our portfolio companies “trian has a strong track record of working with companies to build longterm shareholder value and has been an engaged shareholder we appreciate their perspectives and look forward to a constructive ongoing dialogue with trian as we execute our strategy to reshape the company”  – jeffrey r immelt chairman and ceo of general electric  “we believe that nelson will be a valuable addition to our board we respect his more than  years of business and investment experience as well as his expertise helping consumer products companies leverage their brands and improve operating and financial performance  we welcome his input as we deliver superior shareholder returns”  – irene rosenfeld chairman and ceo of mondelēz “ed brings to our board the perspective of a large and engaged shareholder in bny mellon and has a track record of working collaboratively with other boards and management teams we welcome him and we look forward to benefiting from trian’s insights and contributions as we continue to build value for our clients and shareholders”  – gerald hassell chairman and ceo of bny mellon “we are firmly committed to enhancing value for all sysco shareholders and always welcome constructive input toward driving longterm shareholder value  nelson and josh will bring our board an informed perspective based on their significant experience in the food products industry we have engaged in constructive dialogue with nelson and josh and look forward to benefiting from their insights and contributions”  – jackie ward nonexecutive chairman of sysco’s board of directors “we have maintained an active and constructive dialogue with trian regarding our common goal of increasing shareholder value as we do with all of our shareholders  we believe the addition of ed to our board would bring a shareholder’s perspective and we look forward to benefiting from his insights and trian’s strong analytical work  pentair remains focused on driving productivity and identifying strategic opportunities to position our portfolio for longterm growth”  – randall j hogan chairman and ceo of pentair  ge press release dated october    mondelēztrian press release dated january    bny mellontrian press release dated december    syscotrian press release dated august    pentairtrian press release dated september   download factsheetnelson peltz chief executive officer  founding partnered garden chief investment officer  founding partnerpeter w may president  founding partnerbrian baldwin senior analyst  partnerryan bunch analystkaren chen analystjosh a frank senior analyst  partnerbrian m jacoby senior analyst  partnermark jiang analystdaniel marx assistant general counselvikram nayar analystmatthew peltz senior analyst  partnerwesley roberts analyststuart i rosen general counselstephen rotkiewicz head of tradingstacey sayetta assistant general counselbrian l schorr chief legal officer  partnermeet the teamview our portfolio josh a frank  trian partners toggle navigation trian partners administrator investor reporting josh a frank back to team senior analyst  partnerjosh frank is a partner and senior analyst and has been a member of the investment team of trian since november  mr frank is currently a director of sysco corporation from june  through june  he served as an associate corporate development of triarc companies inc prior to joining triarc mr frank worked at credit suisse first boston from  to  where he spent time in both the mergers  acquisitions and healt