 are experienced business leaders and investment professionals who assist trian with various aspects of its investment process the affiliations listed in the advisory partner bios are included for identification purposes only in october  trian’s legal team was named by the legal  gc powerlist as one of the most influential and innovative inhouse legal teams in the united states alongside teams from major corporations including american express ge att bristol myerssquibb google johnson  johnson kellogg’s jp morgan microsoft nike pepsico shell starbucks and wendy’s home  trian partners toggle navigation trian partners administrator investor reporting highly engaged shareowner “trian has a strong track record of working with companies to build longterm shareholder value and has been an engaged shareholder we appreciate their perspectives and look forward to a constructive ongoing dialogue with trian as we execute our strategy to reshape the company” – jeffrey r immelt chairman and ceo of general electric  ge press release dated october   “we believe that nelson will be a valuable addition to our board we respect his more than  years of business and investment experience as well as his expertise helping consumer products companies leverage their brands and improve operating and financial performance  we welcome his input as we deliver superior shareholder returns” – irene rosenfeld chairman and ceo of mondelēz mondelēztrian press release dated january   “ed brings to our board the perspective of a large and engaged shareholder in bny mellon and has a track record of working collaboratively with other boards and management teams we welcome him and we look forward to benefiting from trian’s insights and contributions as we continue to build value for our clients and shareholders” – gerald hassell chairman and ceo of bny mellon bny mellontrian press release dated december   “we are firmly committed to enhancing value for all sysco shareholders and always welcome constructi